summary: An ordinance authorizing the Superintendent of Buildings to execute a "license agreement" with the United States of America, Dept. of the Army, providing for the use by the City of certain Dept. of Army buildings and facilities in the Seattle Port of Embarkation during construction of Fire Station No. 5, making a reimbursable appropriation from the Emergency Fund in connection therewith and declaring the emergency therefor.
committee: Parks and Public Grounds and Finance
